<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Local Hosting on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/</link><description>Recent content in Local Hosting on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Multipass</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/multipass/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/multipass/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Install &lt;a href="https://multipass.run/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Multipass &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 and Terraform for your operating system. On a Mac (Intel), you can also install via &lt;a href="https://brew.sh/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Homebrew &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 e.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;brew install multipass terraform jq&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clone workshop repository:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;git clone https://github.com/splunk/observability-workshop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Change into Multipass directory:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; observability-workshop/local-hosting/multipass&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Log Observer Connect:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you plan to use your own Splunk Observability Cloud Suite Org and or Splunk instance, you may need to create a new &lt;strong&gt;Log Observer Connect&lt;/strong&gt; connection:
Follow the instructions found in the &lt;a href="https://docs.splunk.com/observability/en/logs/lo-connect-landing.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;documentation &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 for &lt;a href="https://docs.splunk.com/observability/en/logs/scp.html#logs-scp" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Splunk Cloud &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 or &lt;a href="https://docs.splunk.com/observability/en/logs/set-up-logconnect.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Splunk Enterprize &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>OrbStack</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/orbstack/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/orbstack/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Install Orbstack and jq:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;brew install orbstack jq&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clone workshop repository:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;git clone https://github.com/splunk/observability-workshop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Change into Orbstack directory:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; observability-workshop/local-hosting/orbstack&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the script and provide and instance name and &lt;a href="https://swipe.splunk.show" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;SWiPE ID &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 e.g.:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;./start.sh my-instance &lt;span class="m"&gt;12345678&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once the instance has been successfully created (this can take several minutes), you will automatically be logged into the instance. If you exit you can SSH back in using the following command (replace &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;my_instance&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; with the name of your instance):&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Proxmox</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/proxmox/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/resources/local-hosting/proxmox/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="proxmox-workshop-instance-setup"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Proxmox Workshop Instance Setup&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#proxmox-workshop-instance-setup" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="overview"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Overview&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#overview" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;ubuntu-cloud-k3d.sh&lt;/code&gt; script automates the creation of a Splunk Observability Workshop VM on Proxmox VE. It creates a complete Ubuntu 24.04 cloud-init based VM with all necessary tools and configurations pre-installed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id="prerequisites"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#prerequisites" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proxmox VE cluster with administrative access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internet connectivity for downloading cloud images and packages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available VM ID range and storage space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid SWiPE ID for workshop access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Snippets enabled on local storage&lt;/strong&gt; - Required for cloud-init configuration files. To enable:
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In Proxmox web UI, go to &lt;strong&gt;Datacenter → Storage → local&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;Edit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Under &lt;strong&gt;Content&lt;/strong&gt;, add &lt;strong&gt;Snippets&lt;/strong&gt; to the list&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;OK&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id="quick-start"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Quick Start&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#quick-start" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the script directly on your Proxmox host:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>